user_text: Love this place! The food is great and the prices are amazing. I feed my family with less than $20.

I tried their pork with rice and beans and chicken empanada. Absolutely delicious. Really feels like homemade warm food. It was cheap, with a drink costs about $10. More suitable for to go because it has just few counter seats. I was in town for a couple of days definitely would recommend this place over any fancy joints around. People are very friendly. Seemed very popular among locals.
I love the Cereza drink. I get the big bucket. :) And try the club sandwich with fries... either chicken or steak. You can't go wrong!
